  "prompt": "What are some interview tricks for a fresher?",
  "response": "Here are some interview tips for freshers:\n\n1. Preparation Strategies\n- Research the company thoroughly\n- Practice common interview questions\n- Prepare your elevator pitch\n- Know your resume inside out\n- Rehearse with mock interviews\n\n2. Technical Preparation\n- Review fundamentals of your field\n- Solve sample technical questions\n- Be ready to discuss academic projects\n- Demonstrate willingness to learn\n\n3. Communication Tips\n- Maintain positive body language\n- Speak clearly and confidently\n- Listen carefully to questions\n- Ask intelligent questions about the role\n- Show enthusiasm\n\n4. Resume and Presentation\n- Have multiple copies of resume\n- Dress professionally\n- Arrive 10-15 minutes early\n- Carry necessary documents\n- Highlight academic achievements\n\n5. Mindset and Attitude\n- Stay calm and composed\n- Show eagerness to learn\n- Demonstrate problem-solving skills\n- Be honest about limitations\n- Showcase adaptability\n\n6. Follow-up\n- Send a thank-you email\n- Connect on professional networks\n- Request feedback if not selected\n\n7. Additional Skills\n- Highlight interpersonal skills\n- Demonstrate teamwork capabilities\n- Show digital literacy\n- Display soft skills\n\nRemember: Confidence, preparation, and genuine interest are key!",
